"AboutView_Info" = "4champ - Amiga music in your pocket. \n\n4champ connects your device to Amiga Music Preservation website (http://amp.dascene.net) and allows you to search the AMP database for composers, groups and modules. \n\n 4champ uses LibOpenMPT, UADE and HivelyTracker for playback.\n\n 4champ for iOS devices \n© Aleksi Sitomaniemi";

"AboutView_Legal" = "4champ uses Amiga Music Preservation Database with permission granted by the owners of the service.\n\nCopyrights on music belong to the composers. If you think that availability of a given music file in this app violates rights of a 3rd party, please contact AMP staff through amp.dascene.net for a quick withdrawal of said music file.";

"AboutView_Local" = "Modules you have downloaded are listed on Collection tab. Tap a module to start playing it. Long tap will open playlist selector for adding a mod to a playlist.\n\nSwipe left/right on top of a module to delete a module. \n\nYou can sort the local modules list by module type, composer, title, size or favorite status. Use filter button on Local modules page to quickly find the module you're looking for.";

"AboutView_Search" = "Use search to find modules to play. You can search by composer, group or module name, or search from the texts contained in modules. If group search finds only one group, all composers associated with that group are listed. If multiple groups are found, matching groups are listed and selecting one will list the composers. \n\nTap a module to download for playing. \n\nIf you want to keep the module in local collection, tap save icon next right to the module name or set the module as favorite by tapping the star icon. Search results header has a button for downloading all results at one go. You can also start custom radio channel from any search result with modules to listen to them without adding to collection.";

"AboutView_Playlists" = "Playlist view shows the current play queue. When viewing modules on any tab, long tap opens playlist selector where you can add the module to any playlist.\n\nOn playlist view you can control the playback and create/select/clear playlists. You can also select the play mode (sequential/shuffle). \n\nSwipe left will remove the selected module from playlist (but not from Collection).";

"AboutView_Radio" = "4champ radio shuffles songs from the whole AMP database to your device.\n\nIf you like a song that is playing and want to keep it for later, tap the favorite icon (star) on the 4champ radio display view or long tap the module to add to a playlist.\n\nYou can choose from four channels: All (shuffles all content),  New (Recently added to AMP database), Collection (mods from local collection) and Custom (created from a search result)";

"AboutView_Social" ="You can find 4champ on Mastodon! Follow @4champ@mastodon.social for latest news about the app, forthcoming versions, service breaks etc. 4champ feed often has also cool tunes posted for your entertainment. Tap here to follow.";

